args: You're right. ...Hey, Celliera!\nWhat are you up to?
A fool's question. I'm training, of course!
Keeping one's balance is harder when\nrunning on sand, and the harder the\ntraining, the more effective it is!
In other words, running on this beach\nallows me to build up my strength\ntwice as fast as elsewhere.
That is a very ＂you＂ thing to think about.
Yeah, but you're at a BEACH! Doesn't the\nol' bod deserve a rest every now and then?
It's gonna be daunting to students if their\ninstructor is so high-strung all the time.
Hell yeah! Forget all about teachin'\nfor a bit and just play hard!
Then enjoy myself at the beach I shall.\nHuzzah for fun!
Well, now that we've settled that,\nwhat should we do?
How 'bout a game of beach flag?\nWhoever grabs the flag, wins!
*pant* You're way too good at this...\nHow many victories in a row is that?
*huff* *puff* ALL the victories in a row!\nWe ain't won a single time!
Ready to throw in the towel, boys?
I don't know about you, Luca, but I'm\nexhausted. I'm going to sit this one out.
Well, I ain't quitting without ONE win!
If anyone needs me, I'll be passed out\nin the shade over there.
*yaaawn* Hmm... I must've fallen asleep.\nIt's so comfortable here.
I wonder if those two are still...\nHuh? What in the...?
You must be faster, Luca! Faster!
Imagine yourself as a coiled spring and\nuse the energy from your ankles to jump!
...Excellent! Your form has improved!\nNow give me ten laps around the beach.
I am. Er, but what's going on?
I am training Luca so he actually\nhas a chance to defeat me.
Wait. You're training him to...beat you?
Allow me to explain! In all the time you\nhave wasted sleeping, he has not ONCE\nemerged victorious over me.
In the beginning, I merely provided an\nobservation or two and advised him to\ntry a bit of running in the sand.
And at some point that turned into\na full-blown training regimen?
Celliera, is this REALLY how you\nwant to spend your vacation?
Instructing others in how to defeat me?\nOf course! It is the joy of every teacher\nto be defeated by their student!
But you were supposed to put training\naside and relax, remember?
...Ah. That WAS the plan, wasn't it?
And yet I rushed right back into training.\nPerhaps such is just the instructor's fate.
Still, what should I do? I am concerned\nI will simply continue to train and not\nactually ＂enjoy＂ the beach at all.
Well, maybe you could try to make your\ntraining more fun. Give it a seaside\ntheme or something?
Ah! I just thought of something other than\nrunning that might be fun on a beach!
A special kind of training where you\nimprove cardiopulmonary function\nby catching fish while underwater!
We could attempt this activity in that\ncreepy submerged cave I found earlier...
Oh, the possibilities are so exciting!
Heh. I guess nothing perks you up\nmore than the thought of training.
Still, so long as you enjoy the beach in\nyour own way, I guess that's what matters.
Right then! Time to go have fun\nat the beach, Celliera style!
...Oh, wait. There's one thing\nI have to do before I go.
Then it's time for one more game\nof beach flag!
Ha! I win again! You will have\nto do better than that, Luca!
She can't hold back in training OR play...
